It has a great dog water-fountain. It\'s closed for part of the summer (check the web site for the exact dates each year).

properties.name: My first car accident
properties.description: Posted by JaheadThis is where I got into my first car accident. I was in my VW bug and I hit a guy in a very large pickup truck from behind. His truck didn\'t get damaged at all, but my front was very smashed in (it looked like a muppet afterwards). He left without calling the police, since he had no damage. That was nice of him.

properties.name: Where I almost got mugged
properties.description: Posted by JaheadIt was around 12 am and very dark in November 1994. I was walking home after hanging out with some people. A guy on a bicycle and a guy on foot were approaching. I crossed the street because they were being loud (and were seemingly drunk). I didn\'t want to interact with them. Then, just as we reached each other, one of them ran across the street and pushed me. I was stunned. I just stood there. I had my backpack with me and the guy on the bicycle said, "Don\'t bother this guy dude, he doesn\'t have anything." Then they just continued down Beaver Street.

properties.description: Posted by JaheadEdinburghI gave a talk here about partial satisfaction of numeric goals in planning. I had a great time there, too.

properties.name: Where my eyes were opened to the world
properties.description: Posted by Jahead Buckingham Palace Road, London, SW1EI arrived very early via plane. I had barely slept during the last 20 hours. I had to take a train to "Victoria Station". During the train ride, it was pitch black when I looked out the window. When I entered the station, it just looked like a mall area. The sun must have risen since the train ride. When I existed the station, I couldn\'t believe it. I was initially overwelmed by London. Then I and a friend realized we had 5 mile walk to our hostel...and we wouldn\'t be able to sleep for many more hours.

properties.name: Where we found Molly, the dog
properties.description: Posted by Jahead10005 E. Osborn Rd., ScottsdaleShe was a little puppy--13 lbs. Probably 2 or 3 months old at the time in July 2001. She was following a couple of people who were ignoring her. She just wanted some love, but she had mange and ticks all over her (and tick fever, we found out later), she also had a broken hip and is deaf... She got fixed up and is a very nice dog (to people she knows). Yay! I love her a lot. She likes the dog parks we go to on the weekends.
